A grandmother has today spoken of her shock at finding a dead lizard wrapped in a cucumber she bought at Aldi.

Jenny Wilkinson, 54, was about to chop up the vegetable and give it to her one-year-old grandson, Theo, when she spotted an unusual mark near the top.

Upon further inspection, she realised the strange brown patch was a lizard that had been squashed in to the cucumber when it was vacuum-packed.

